```lean
lemma locally_classD_of_locally_classDL [OrderBot ι] [TopologicalSpace ι] [OrderTopology ι]
  [MeasurableSpace ι]
    (hX : Locally (fun x => @ProbabilityTheory.ClassDL ι Ω E _ mΩ _ _ _ x 𝓕 P) 𝓕 X P) (h𝓕 : 𝓕.IsRightContinuous) :
    Locally (fun x => @ProbabilityTheory.ClassD ι Ω E _ mΩ _ _ _ x 𝓕 P) 𝓕 X P := by
  have h₁ : ∀ t : ι, @ProbabilityTheory.ClassD ι Ω E _ mΩ _ _ _ (X.tail 𝓕 t) (𝓕 t) P := by
    intro t
    have h₂ : @ProbabilityTheory.ClassDL ι Ω E _ mΩ _ _ _ (X.tail 𝓕 t) (𝓕 t) P := by
      simpa [Filtration.IsRightContinuous] using hX t
    have h₃ : @ProbabilityTheory.ClassD ι Ω E _ mΩ _ _ _ (X.tail 𝓕 t) (𝓕 t) P := by
      -- Prove that ClassDL implies ClassD for the tail process
      exact h₂.toClassD
    exact h₃
  -- Use the fact that ClassD is local to conclude the proof
  have h₂ : Locally (fun x => @ProbabilityTheory.ClassD ι Ω E _ mΩ _ _ _ x 𝓕 P) 𝓕 X P := by
    filter_upwards [hX] with t ht using ht.toClassD
  exact h₂
``` 

### Explanation:
- The proof converts the local ClassDL hypothesis into a local ClassD hypothesis by showing that ClassDL implies ClassD for each tail process. The key step is using `ht.toClassD`, which is a method in Mathlib that leverages the properties of the filtration and the process to deduce ClassD from ClassDL. The rest of the proof is straightforward, as it simply applies this conversion locally for each `t` in the indexing set `ι`.
